hook.real_world_problem:
```java
// Flipkart's product description formatter — SLOW:
String result = "";
for (char c : description.toCharArray()) {
    if (Character.isLetterOrDigit(c)) result += c; // O(n²)!!
}
// n=100,000 chars: 10^10 operations = system timeout

// FAST — StringBuilder:
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
for (char c : description.toCharArray()) {
    if (Character.isLetterOrDigit(c)) sb.append(c); // O(n)
}
String result = sb.toString();
// n=100,000: 100,000 operations = milliseconds
```

concept_explanation.immutability:
**String is immutable — every modification creates a new object:**

```java
// What String += actually does:
String s = "hello";
s += " world"; // creates new String("hello world"), discards old

// In a loop over n characters — O(n²):
String result = "";
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    result += arr[i]; // step i: copies (i) chars + adds 1 = O(i)
}
// Total: 0+1+2+...+(n-1) = n(n-1)/2 = O(n²)

// StringBuilder — O(n):
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    sb.append(arr[i]); // O(1) amortized
}
String result = sb.toString(); // one final copy O(n)
```

